SHOTGUN WORKFLOW

2025-04-03

This scripts present the different steps used for the analysis of shotgun data used in the paper “Comparison of metabarcoding and shotgun sequencing confirms the relevance of chloroplastic barcodes for lake phytoplankton diversity assessment” (Lemonnier et al., in prep)

Quality filtering


# using the first step of Anvio metagenomic workflow
# with Anvio-8

anvi-run-workflow -w metagenomics -c qual.json --skip-dry-run -A --until gzip_fastqs

SILVA database curation


# SILVA database : 138.1 NR99

# Replace "U" by "T" in SILVA db sequences
awk '/^[^>]/{ gsub(/U/,"T") }1' SILVA_138.1_SSURef_NR99_tax_silva.fasta > SILVA_138.1_SSURef_NR99_tax_silva_DNA.fasta

# Fix non standard characters using the python script of Ribotaxa (Chakoory et al., 2022)
python fix_nonstandard_chars.py <SILVA_138.1_SSURef_NR99_tax_silva.fasta> SILVA_138.1_SSURef_NR99_tax_silva_nschars.fasta

# Mask low-complexity and repeated sequences using bbmask
# BBMap v39.01
bbmask.sh in=SILVA_138.1_LSURef_NR99_tax_silva_nschars.fasta out=SILVA_138.1_LSURef_NR99_tax_silva_nschars_masked.fasta overwrite=t minkr=4 maxkr=8 minlen=20 minke=4 maxke=8 entropy=0.70 threads=8

# Remove sequences corresponding to the wrong ribosomal subunit with nhmmer based on hmm files from PhyloFlash (Gruber-Vodicka et al., 2020)
# HMMER v3.2.1
nhmmer -o /dev/null --tblout SILVA_138.1_LSURef_NR99_nschars_masked_hmmer_lsu_output.txt -E 1e-6 --cpu 8 ssu_ABE.hmm SILVA_138.1_LSURef_NR99_tax_silva_nschars_masked.fasta

# We extract sequence id from the nhmmer output file
awk '{print $1}' SILVA_138.1_LSURef_NR99_nschars_masked_hmmer_ssu_output.txt > ids_ssu.txt  

# And remove them in the SILVA db fasta file
awk 'BEGIN{while((getline<"ids_ssu.txt")>0)l[">"$1]=1}/^>/{f=!l[$1]}f' SILVA_138.1_LSURef_NR99_tax_silva_nschars_masked.fasta > SILVA_138.1_LSURef_NR99_tax_silva_nschars_masked_noSSU.fasta

# Finally, putative vectors are removed using bbduck
# BBMap v39.01
bbduk.sh in=SILVA_138.1_LSURef_NR99_tax_silva_nschars_masked_noSSU.fasta out=SILVA_138.1_LSURef_NR99_tax_silva_nschars_masked_noSSU_noV.fasta ref=UniVec_NCBI.fa overwrite=t fastawrap=0 ktrim=r ow=t minlength=800 mink=11 hdist=1

Extract rRNA reads with SortMeRNA

# Exemple of extracting LSU rRNA reads for one sample
# It was done in parallel in the server

sortmerna -ref SILVA_138.1_LSURef_NR99_tax_silva_nschars_masked_noSSU_noV.fasta -reads Ann01-QUALITY_PASSED_R1.fastq.gz -reads Ann01-QUALITY_PASSED_R2.fastq.gz -workdir 04_SORTMERNA/LSU -min_lis 10 -e 1e-9 -threads 16 -fastx -aligned $sample-LSU-rRNA

Get the number of extracted reads

# Cat LSU reads names of all sample in a single table
raw.files <- tibble(filename = list.files('Results/SortMeRNA/LSU/'))
raw.files$filename <- gsub("-SILVA-LSU-Blast.txt","",raw.files$filename)
raw.files$filename <- gsub("-LSU-id.txt","",raw.files$filename)
raw.files <- raw.files[rowid(raw.files$filename) <= 1,]

# Create a data.frame with the same dimensions and colnames as the final result
columns = c("seqid","sample") 
Sample_ID_all <- data.frame(matrix(nrow = 0, ncol = length(columns))) 
colnames(Sample_ID_all) = columns

# Create a table with all samples reads
for (f in raw.files$filename) {
  Sample_ID <- read.table(paste0( "Results/SortMeRNA/LSU/", f, "-LSU-id.txt"), sep="\t")
  Sample_ID$V1 <- gsub(">","",Sample_ID$V1)
  colnames(Sample_ID) <- c("seqid")
  Sample_ID$sample <- paste0("", f)
  Sample_ID_all <- rbind(Sample_ID_all, Sample_ID)
}

saveRDS(Sample_ID_all, "Results/SortMeRNA/LSU/Sample_ID_all_LSU.rds")


# Get number of reads per sample
Sample_ID_all$nseq <- 1

LSU <- Sample_ID_all %>%
  group_by(sample) %>%
  summarise(nLSUreads = sum(nseq))

nreadsrRNA <- merge(LSU,SSU, by="sample")

Blast rRNA reads


# Exemple for LSU
# Taxonomic assignment are done on SILVA LSU and Phytool 23S
# For SSU, taxonomic assignment were done on SILVA SSU, Phytool 16S and Phytool 18S

# Using blastn
# NCBI_Blast+ v2.15.0

# Blast on SILVA db
blastn -query Ann01-LSU-rRNA.fasta -subject SILVA_138.1_SSURef_NR99_tax_silva_nschars_masked_noLSU_noV.fasta -num_threads 11 -outfmt '6 qseqid sseqid length pident gapopen mismatch evalue' -max_target_seqs 10 -out Ann01-SILVA-LSU-Blast.txt

# Blast on Phytool 23S db (https://github-carrtel.shinyapps.io/phytool_v2/)
blastn -query Ann03-LSU-rRNA.fasta -subject Phytool_complete_rRNA_23S_2024-01-15.fasta -num_threads 4 -outfmt '6 qseqid sseqid length pident gapopen mismatch evalue' -max_target_seqs 10 -out Ann01-Phytool-23S-Blast-LSU.txt

Keep only high quality hits

# Exemple for SSU 16S

# Load path for Blast results

raw.files <- tibble(filename = list.files('Results/SortMeRNA/Phytool_16S/'))

raw.files$filename <- gsub("-Phytool-16S-Blast-SSU.txt","",raw.files$filename)


# Create a data.frame with the same dimensions and colnames as the final result
columns = c("kingdom","phylum","class","order","family","genus","species","seqid","database","sample") 
Phytool_16S_all_samples <- data.frame(matrix(nrow = 0, ncol = length(columns))) 
colnames(Phytool_16S_all_samples) = columns

for (f in raw.files$filename) {
  # Load SILVA LSU blast results
  Blast_table_Phytool_16S <- read.table(paste0( "Results/SortMeRNA/Phytool_16S/", f, "-Phytool-16S-Blast-SSU.txt"), sep="\t")
  # Subset based on match length and percent identity
  Blast_table_Phytool_16S <- subset(Blast_table_Phytool_16S, V3 >= 140 & V4 >= 95 & V5 <= 1 & V6 <= 1)
  # Separate taxo
  septaxo <- as.data.frame(str_split_fixed(Blast_table_Phytool_16S$V2, ';', 7))
  septaxo$seqid <- Blast_table_Phytool_16S$V1
  colnames(septaxo) <- c("kingdom","phylum","class","order","family","genus","species","seqid")
  # Keep first 10 hits
  septaxo_Phytool_16S <- septaxo[rowid(septaxo$seqid) <= 10,]
  # Check if phylum is the same for these 10 hits
  septaxo_Phytool_16S$is_phylum_conserved <- septaxo_Phytool_16S$phylum
  septaxo_Phytool_16S <- septaxo_Phytool_16S %>%
  group_by(seqid) %>%
  mutate(is_phylum_conserved = replace(is_phylum_conserved, n_distinct(is_phylum_conserved)==1, TRUE))
  # Keep only reads with conserved phylum
  taxtable_Phytool_16S_final <- subset(septaxo_Phytool_16S, is_phylum_conserved=="TRUE")
  # Keep the first hit result only
  taxtable_Phytool_16S_final <- taxtable_Phytool_16S_final[rowid(taxtable_Phytool_16S_final$seqid) <= 1,]
  taxtable_Phytool_16S_final <- taxtable_Phytool_16S_final[,-9]
  # Add some useful informations
  taxtable_Phytool_16S_final$database <- "PHYTOOL_16S"
  taxtable_Phytool_16S_final$sample <- paste0("", f)
  taxtable_Phytool_16S_final$Phytool16S_length <- Blast_table_Phytool_16S[match(taxtable_Phytool_16S_final$seqid, Blast_table_Phytool_16S$V1),"V3"]
  taxtable_Phytool_16S_final$Phytool16S_pident <- Blast_table_Phytool_16S[match(taxtable_Phytool_16S_final$seqid, Blast_table_Phytool_16S$V1),"V4"]
  Phytool_16S_all_samples <- rbind(Phytool_16S_all_samples, taxtable_Phytool_16S_final)
}
  
saveRDS(Phytool_16S_all_samples, "Results/SortMeRNA/Phytool_16S/Phytool_16S_all_samples_length_140_pident_95.RDS")

Compare the number of reads assigned within each phylum

# Load metadata
metadata <- read.table("Results/Metadata/metadata_OLA.csv", header=T, row.names=1, sep=";")

# 23S 

Phytool_23S_good <- readRDS("Results/SortMeRNA/Final_tables/LSU_Phytool_23S_all_samples_good.RDS")

table_23S <- as.data.frame(Phytool_23S_good)

table_23S$lake <- metadata[match(table_23S$sample.x, metadata$sampleID),"Lac"]
table_23S$Date <- metadata[match(table_23S$sample.x, metadata$sampleID),"Date"]


table_23S$nseq <- 1

d23S <- as.data.frame(table_23S) %>%
  group_by(lake, Date, order.x) %>%
  summarise(shotgun23S = sum(nseq)) %>%
  group_by(lake, Date,) %>%
  mutate(shotgun23S = round(shotgun23S / sum(shotgun23S)*100, 3)) 

colnames(d23S) <- c("lake","Date","order","shotgun23S")

d23S$ID <- paste0(d23S$order, d23S$lake, d23S$Date, sep="|")
d23S <- as.data.frame(d23S)

# 16S

Phytool_16S_good <- readRDS("Results/SortMeRNA/Final_tables/Phytool_16S_good.RDS")

table_16S <- as.data.frame(Phytool_16S_good)
table_16S$lake <- metadata[match(table_16S$sample, metadata$sampleID),"Lac"]
table_16S$Date <- metadata[match(table_16S$sample, metadata$sampleID),"Date"]
table_16S$nseq <- 1


d16S <- as.data.frame(table_16S) %>%
  group_by(lake, Date, order) %>%
  summarise(shotgun16S = sum(nseq)) %>%
  group_by(lake, Date,) %>%
  mutate(shotgun16S = round(shotgun16S / sum(shotgun16S )*100, 3)) 

d16S$ID <- paste0(d16S$order, d16S$lake, d16S$Date, sep="|")
d16S <- as.data.frame(d16S)

d23S$shotgun16S <- d16S[match(d23S$ID, d16S$ID),"shotgun16S"]
d23S[is.na(d23S$shotgun16S),"shotgun16S"] <- 0
